CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 20, 1961, pg. 2 reads: "13th Ward Winner, Backers - Leo Washington, third from left, who was supported by his brother, Ward Chairman Linn Washington, second from left, for the Democratic constable nomination, won easily over all opponents in his ward. Left to right: Wendell Allen, Linn Washington, Lee Washington, Gerald Fox, secretary of the ward committee, and Leo McLaughlin, representative in the Pennsylvania Assembly, from the same area, are shown at Belmar School polls in the Third District, 13th Ward."
TitMainTitle: Wendell Allen, Linn Washington, Lee Washington, Gerald Fox, and Leo McLaughlin standing in front of Belmar School next to large campaign poster during 1961 primary elections
